name: integer_u32_above_u16_maximum
description: |
  This is one above u16 maximum, represented as u32. Narrowing it to
  u16 may reject, saturate, or wrap to zero. It also catches serializers,
  FFI layers, and intermediate expressions that silently retain only the lower
  16 bits.
format: hex
decode-as: u32
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u32"
  - "lower-width"
  - "boundary"
  - "overflow"
  - "narrowing"
  - "truncation"
---
00 00 01 00   # 65536
